00:21:15,685 --> 00:21:17,903
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

444
00:21:17,954 --> 00:21:20,489
DOESN'T MATTER ANYWAY.
IT'S ALL OKAY NOW.

445
00:21:21,792 --> 00:21:24,410
BY THE WAY, DAD WANTS
TO PASS THROUGH NEW YORK

446
00:21:24,461 --> 00:21:26,245
ON ONE OF HIS
UPCOMING TRIPS.

447
00:21:26,296 --> 00:21:30,198
DO ME A FAVOR-- DON'T GET HIM
A ROOM AT THE CHELSEA HOTEL.

448
00:21:30,216 --> 00:21:32,217
YOU KNOW, I STILL NEVER
KNOW WHAT TO SAY TO HIM.

449
00:21:32,251 --> 00:21:33,918
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TALK
TO YOUR FATHER.

450
00:21:33,969 --> 00:21:36,871
HE'S SUCH A CONVERSATIONALIST,
HE'LL TAKE CARE OF THE WHOLE THING.

451
00:21:36,889 --> 00:21:40,508
BUT THAT'S NOT
ACTUALLY TALKING, MOM.

452
00:21:40,542 --> 00:21:43,060
YOU KNOW,
THAT'S KILLING TIME.

453
00:21:43,094 --> 00:21:46,063
WELL, SOMETIMES

454
00:21:46,097 --> 00:21:48,849
THAT'S THE BEST
YOU CAN ASK FOR.

455
00:21:58,391 --> 00:22:00,893
THE BOYS
ARE SO SO LAZY.

456
00:22:00,911 --> 00:22:04,864
BUT YOU HAVE TO TRY TO
LEAD THEM AS FAR AS YOU CAN.

457
00:22:04,898 --> 00:22:08,251
YOU STILL HAVE ALL THAT
HEAVY EQUIPMENT TO GET?

458
00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:11,621
OH, HELLO.

459
00:22:11,672 --> 00:22:13,238
WELCOME HOME,
PATRICIA.

460
00:22:13,256 --> 00:22:15,406
OH, YOU'RE A VISION.

461
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:19,261
DID YOU MAKE YOUR
CONNECTING FLIGHT OKAY?

462
00:22:19,295 --> 00:22:21,429
WHY, YES, WE DID.

463
00:22:23,015 --> 00:22:26,801
OH.

464
00:22:26,852 --> 00:22:28,602
DID YOU MAKE YOUR
CONNECTING FLIGHT OKAY?

465
00:22:28,637 --> 00:22:30,104
YES.

466
00:22:30,138 --> 00:22:32,439
HOW ABOUT I TAKE YOU GUYS
TO LUNCH? YOU LOOK EXHAUSTED.

467
00:22:32,474 --> 00:22:34,608
THEY CAN'T SPEAK TO YOU
WHEN THEY'RE FILMING, BILL.

468
00:22:34,643 --> 00:22:36,277
OH, TAKE TWO.

469
00:22:36,311 --> 00:22:38,696
HOW ABOUT I TAKE MY
BEAUTIFUL WIFE TO LUNCH?

470
00:22:38,730 --> 00:22:42,899
- ON CAMERA OR OFF?
- MY LIFE'S AN OPEN BOOK.

471
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:45,285
OH, DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT.
WE'LL PUT A LITTLE CAMI BEHIND IT

472
00:22:45,319 --> 00:22:47,403
AND EVERYTHING WILL BE
ABSOLUTELY FINE.

473
00:22:49,273 --> 00:22:50,540
WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR A MINUTE?

474
00:22:50,574 --> 00:22:52,292
MICHELLE,
WOULD YOU PLEASE?

475
00:22:52,326 --> 00:22:55,245
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO TRY IT ON?

476
00:22:55,279 --> 00:22:58,714
PATS.
PATSY.

477
00:22:58,748 --> 00:23:01,683
- VAL, HI.
- HI THERE, VAL.

478
00:23:01,718 --> 00:23:04,119
- BILL.
- HI THERE, VAL.

479
00:23:04,137 --> 00:23:06,338
SO I WAS GOING
TO CALL YOU.

480
00:23:06,389 --> 00:23:07,789
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS UP TO?

481
00:23:07,807 --> 00:23:10,008
OH, JUST GRABBING
A BITE AT EL PASEO.

482
00:23:10,059 --> 00:23:11,893
WELL, DO STOP BY
WHEN YOU'RE DONE.

483
00:23:11,927 --> 00:23:13,978
I CAN SET YOU UP
WITH A NEW SPRING OUTFIT,

484
00:23:14,012 --> 00:23:16,180
COMPLETE WITH PURSE,
HAT AND SHOES,

485
00:23:16,231 --> 00:23:17,598
ALL ON THE HOUSE.

486
00:23:17,632 --> 00:23:19,466
OH MY GOODNESS.
WHY?

487
00:23:19,484 --> 00:23:22,737
BECAUSE I'D LOVE AMERICA TO
SEE MY NEW SPRING LINE IS WHY.

488
00:23:24,306 --> 00:23:26,406
AND BILL PROMISED HE COULD
GET ME A WARDROBE CREDIT.

489
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,909
OH, THAT'S MY BILL.

490
00:23:28,943 --> 00:23:31,027
- DID I?
- ALWAYS FULL OF PROMISES.

491
00:23:31,078 --> 00:23:33,613
WELL WELL WELL,
IT'S AMERICA'S PERFECT FAMILY.

492
00:23:33,647 --> 00:23:37,317
- HI THERE, JEREMY. HOW'S IT GOING?
- HI, BILL.

493
00:23:37,335 --> 00:23:39,669
- SO NICE TO SEE YOU.
- HI.

494
00:23:39,704 --> 00:23:42,338
HOW DOES IT FEEL
TO BE A MOVIE STAR?

495
00:23:42,372 --> 00:23:44,990
WELL...

496
00:23:46,626 --> 00:23:49,345
YOU GOT A NICE TAN
WHILE I WAS AWAY.

497
00:23:49,379 --> 00:23:52,131
HIGH BLOOD PRESSURE,
KIDDO.

498
00:23:52,165 --> 00:23:53,933
THIS STRIKE'S
GONNA DO ME IN.

499
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:55,383
ARE WE GONNA
GO BROKE, BILL?

500
00:23:55,434 --> 00:23:58,887
YOU BETTER BELIEVE IT.
LANCE LIVING IT UP IN NEW YORK--

501
00:23:58,938 --> 00:24:00,772
I HOPE HE KNOWS HE'S
ON A SHORT STRING THERE.

502
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:02,774
WE JUST DON'T HAVE
THE MONEY ANYMORE.

503
00:24:02,808 --> 00:24:04,675
HE LOVES MANHATTAN.

504
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:07,362
HE'S SO HAPPY HE BURSTS
INTO SONG SOMETIMES.

505
00:24:07,396 --> 00:24:09,280
HE HAS SUCH
A SPARK OF LIFE,

506
00:24:09,315 --> 00:24:11,315
LIKE NO ONE
I'VE EVER KNOWN,

507
00:24:11,349 --> 00:24:13,233
SO OPEN AND FUNNY.

508
00:24:13,284 --> 00:24:14,785
THAT'S GREAT,

509
00:24:14,819 --> 00:24:17,020
BUT HE'S GOT TO START
THINKING ABOUT A JOB TOO.

510
00:24:17,038 --> 00:24:19,039
THESE KIDS GOT TO LEARN
THE VALUE OF WORK.

511
00:24:19,073 --> 00:24:22,859
I TELL GRANT THAT HE CAN
MAKE $10 AN HOUR

512
00:24:22,877 --> 00:24:25,211
HAULING CEMENT FOR DAVID WITZELL,
AND YOU KNOW WHAT HE DOES?

513
00:24:25,245 --> 00:24:27,413
HE GIVES ME THAT
WOLFMAN JACK DOG CALL--

514
00:24:27,464 --> 00:24:29,531
"NO WAY, BROTHER.
NO WAY.

515
00:24:29,549 --> 00:24:33,052
I'M STAYING RIGHT HERE AND
I'M PLAYING WITH THE BAND."

516
00:24:33,086 --> 00:24:35,888
THAT BAND IS
HIS DREAM, BILL.

517
00:24:35,923 --> 00:24:38,040
WELL, OKAY, BUT HOW ABOUT
FINDING A DREAM

518
00:24:38,058 --> 00:24:40,375
THAT BRINGS IN
SOME BUCKS?

519
00:24:43,545 --> 00:24:47,098
WELL, HOW ABOUT
RAISING PEOPLE

520
00:24:47,149 --> 00:24:49,100
THAT HAVE A SHOT
AT BEING HAPPY?

521
00:24:55,273 --> 00:24:57,491
HOW ABOUT HAVING PARENTS
THAT MAKE CERTAIN

522
00:24:57,525 --> 00:24:59,944
THEIR KIDS KNOW THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN RIGHT AND WRONG,

523
00:24:59,995 --> 00:25:01,612
WHAT THEY SHOULD
AND SHOULDN'T DO?

524
00:25:01,663 --> 00:25:04,564
I THINK THAT WOULD BE
NICE TOO, DON'T YOU?

525
00:25:06,418 --> 00:25:08,835
I KNOW THESE GUYS THINK
YOUR LITTLE ESCAPADE

526
00:25:08,869 --> 00:25:10,586
IN NEW YORK
WAS MORE EXCITING

527
00:25:10,621 --> 00:25:13,006
THAN FILMING ME
HOLDING DOWN THE FORT HERE,

528
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:15,291
BUT BELIEVE ME,
THIS WEEK OF BABYSITTING

529
00:25:15,342 --> 00:25:19,595
GAVE ME A BETTER IDEA OF
WHAT GOES ON WHEN I'M GONE.

530
00:25:19,630 --> 00:25:21,414
REALLY?
LIKE WHAT?

531
00:25:21,432 --> 00:25:23,298
LIKE A 16-YEAR-OLD
DAUGHTER

532
00:25:23,349 --> 00:25:25,717
THAT STAYS OUT HALF THE NIGHT
AFTER A DANCE PRACTICE--

533
00:25:25,751 --> 00:25:29,554
2:00 A.M.
ON A SCHOOL NIGHT, PAT?

534
00:25:29,588 --> 00:25:32,924
SURE, IT'S FUN AND EASY
BEING FRIENDS WITH YOUR KIDS,

535
00:25:32,942 --> 00:25:36,594
BUT HOW ABOUT GIVING THEM
A LITTLE STRUCTURE?

536
00:25:39,815 --> 00:25:42,599
THIS CONVERSATION
WILL END RIGHT HERE.

537
00:25:43,702 --> 00:25:45,436
I'LL SPEAK TO CRAIG
IN THE MORNING

538
00:25:45,454 --> 00:25:47,655
ABOUT DROPPING THIS
FROM THE FILM.

539
00:25:49,041 --> 00:25:51,125
BAIT ME IN FRONT
OF THE CAMERA AGAIN

540
00:25:51,159 --> 00:25:53,660
AND YOU'LL BE
VERY VERY SORRY, BILL.

541
00:25:59,417 --> 00:26:02,719
So you let her walk off
just like that?

542
00:26:02,753 --> 00:26:05,288
CRAIG, SHE LEFT
ON HER OWN VOLITION.

543
00:26:05,306 --> 00:26:07,589
I CAN'T INTERFERE WITH
THE EVENTS AS THEY'RE HAPPENING.

544
00:26:07,623 --> 00:26:09,008
WELL, YOU COULD'VE
FOLLOWED HER.

545
00:26:09,059 --> 00:26:11,343
There was finally
genuine drama unfolding

546
00:26:11,394 --> 00:26:12,627
AND YOU DIDN'T
GET IT ON FILM.

547
00:26:12,645 --> 00:26:14,430
BELIEVE ME,
WE GOT PLENTY ON FILM.

548
00:26:14,464 --> 00:26:17,433
Well, actually I think you
barely scratched the surface.

549
00:26:17,467 --> 00:26:18,967
AND I DON'T APPRECIATE
THIS ATTITUDE.

550
00:26:18,985 --> 00:26:20,519
This isn't about
an attitude.

551
00:26:20,570 --> 00:26:22,470
THIS IS ABOUT
DOCUMENTARY ETHICS.

552
00:26:22,488 --> 00:26:24,472
Alan, your job is
to film the Louds--

553
00:26:24,490 --> 00:26:27,492
NO JUDGMENTS, NO INVOLVEMENTS,
NO PERSONAL FEELINGS.

554
00:26:27,526 --> 00:26:31,145
- I know-- - THAT'S WHAT W.N.E.T.
CONTRACTED YOU FOR

555
00:26:31,163 --> 00:26:34,449
AND THAT'S WHERE YOUR
ETHICAL RESPONSIBILITY LIES.

556
00:26:34,483 --> 00:26:36,166
SO LET'S GET
ON THE SAME PAGE HERE

557
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:38,952
AND YOU SHOOT WHAT I NEED
TO MAKE A SUCCESSFUL FILM.

558
00:26:38,986 --> 00:26:41,821
- HAVE A NICE DAY.
THANK YOU. - Okay, Craig--

559
00:26:41,839 --> 00:26:44,207
WHEN CRAIG GILBERT
HIRED US,

560
00:26:44,258 --> 00:26:46,626
WE HAD NO IDEA WHAT
WE WERE GETTING INTO.

561
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:48,128
FIRST OF ALL,
WE WERE JUST MARRIED

562
00:26:48,162 --> 00:26:50,763
AND I THINK WE HAD SOMETHING
A LITTLE MORE EXOTIC IN MIND

563
00:26:50,797 --> 00:26:53,132
FOR OUR HONEYMOON THAN
A ROOMFUL OF FILM EQUIPMENT.

564
00:26:53,166 --> 00:26:54,934
WHAT MADE YOU
CHANGE YOUR MIND?

565
00:26:54,968 --> 00:26:57,770
THE SUBJECT MATTER, I THINK--
FOR ME ANYWAY.

566
00:26:57,804 --> 00:27:00,723
FOR ME IT WAS THE CHANCE
TO BE ABLE TO DO SOMETHING PURE--

567
00:27:00,774 --> 00:27:03,359
CINEMA VERITE,
THE CINEMA OF TRUTH.

568
00:27:03,393 --> 00:27:05,527
HEY, DAD,
YOUR TAXI'S HERE.

569
00:27:05,561 --> 00:27:07,529
- OKAY, HONEY.

570
00:27:07,563 --> 00:27:10,065
ALL RIGHT,
I GOTTA GO.

571
00:27:10,116 --> 00:27:11,516
HELLO?

572
00:27:11,534 --> 00:27:14,536
HI, LANCE!

573
00:27:14,570 --> 00:27:16,654
GUYS, IT'S LANCE.
HE'S CALLING COLLECT.

574
00:27:16,688 --> 00:27:18,323
ACCEPT THE CHARGES,
SWEETIE.

575
00:27:18,357 --> 00:27:20,024
- HELLO?
- Hi!

576
00:27:20,042 --> 00:27:21,191
HI, GUYS.

577
00:27:21,209 --> 00:27:23,360
I have very
exciting news.

578
00:27:23,378 --> 00:27:24,878
WHAT IS IT, HONEY?
DID YOU GET A JOB?

579
00:27:24,913 --> 00:27:26,530
I'M GOING TO PARIS.

580
00:27:26,548 --> 00:27:30,217
- PARIS?
- HE GOT A JOB IN PARIS?

581
00:27:30,251 --> 00:27:31,919
LANCE, ARE YOU
IN HIGH SPIRITS AGAIN?

582
00:27:31,970 --> 00:27:34,837
Am I-- am I--?
Yes, I am in high spirits!

583
00:27:34,871 --> 00:27:36,705
LANCE, LANCE,
IT'S DAD.

584
00:27:36,723 --> 00:27:38,674
- Hi, Dad. - WHAT ARE
YOU DOING IN PARIS?

585
00:27:38,708 --> 00:27:41,677
I AM DOING STREET THEATER.
THAT'S WHAT I'M DOING.

586
00:27:41,711 --> 00:27:44,480
I'M DOING IT WITH THIS
REALLY REALLY SUPER
GROUP OF PEOPLE.

587
00:27:44,515 --> 00:27:46,849
IS THAT ONE OF THOSE
"UP WITH PEOPLE" KIND OF DEALS?

588
00:27:46,883 --> 00:27:49,768
You know, I didn't ask,
but I tell them how great you are,

589
00:27:49,819 --> 00:27:51,653
not that I don't say
that Mother isn't.

590
00:27:51,687 --> 00:27:54,156
In fact, I think I say that
Mother's a bit greater even than you,

591
00:27:54,190 --> 00:27:55,907
but you know what I mean.
Hold on a second.

592
00:27:55,942 --> 00:27:59,244
HEY, GUYS,
GET ME A TOASTED ALMOND.

593
00:27:59,278 --> 00:28:00,445
OKAY, HONEY.

594
00:28:00,496 --> 00:28:04,498
- CATCH.
- OH, WE'RE RICH!

595
00:28:04,533 --> 00:28:07,034
- Lance.
- WHAT?

596
00:28:07,068 --> 00:28:09,453
I WOULD LIKE TO KNOW
WHO'S FINANCING THIS TRIP.

597
00:28:09,504 --> 00:28:11,422
OH, UH,

598
00:28:11,456 --> 00:28:13,424
THIS REALLY
REALLY NICE,

599
00:28:13,458 --> 00:28:17,511
VERY RICH MAN WHOSE NAME
I DON'T REMEMBER.

600
00:28:17,546 --> 00:28:20,263
- HE'S NOT GOING TO PARIS.
- Maybe it's--  oh, I don't know.

601
00:28:20,297 --> 00:28:23,249
- I GOTTA GO.
- Paul or John or Ringo

602
00:28:23,267 --> 00:28:24,434
OR SOMETHING.

603
00:28:24,468 --> 00:28:25,935
HE'S NOT GOING
TO PARIS.

604
00:28:25,970 --> 00:28:28,271
HONEY, YOUR FATHER SAYS
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO PARIS.

605
00:28:28,305 --> 00:28:30,423
I'M ACTUALLY FLATTERED.

606
00:28:30,441 --> 00:28:33,109
NO ONE'S EVER
TOLD ME THAT BEFORE.

607
00:28:35,111 --> 00:28:37,930
Lance, honey,
how are you really?

608
00:28:37,964 --> 00:28:40,899
Have you been taking
care of that cold?

609
00:28:40,933 --> 00:28:42,934
I JUST NEED YOU TO BE
A LITTLE MORE PATIENT.

610
00:28:42,952 --> 00:28:45,871
YOU'RE BURNING 18 ROLLS
OF FILM PER DAY.

611
00:28:45,905 --> 00:28:49,323
YOU'RE WAY OVER BUDGET AND
YOU'RE NOT GETTING ENOUGH DRAMA.

612
00:28:49,374 --> 00:28:51,159
NOW I THINK WE'VE BEEN
MORE THAN PATIENT.

613
00:28:51,210 --> 00:28:53,127
A HUGE PART OF THIS PROCESS
IS ESTABLISHING

614
00:28:53,162 --> 00:28:56,714
A COMFORTABLE RELATIONSHIP
BETWEEN THE SUBJECT AND THE CAMERA.

615
00:28:56,748 --> 00:28:59,217
SO MAYBE YOU SHOULD
HEAD OUT TO SANTA BARBARA

616
00:28:59,251 --> 00:29:01,802
AND JUST PUSH THAT
RELATIONSHIP ALONG.

617
00:29:03,304 --> 00:29:05,288
WELCOME HOME.

618
00:29:05,306 --> 00:29:07,924
OH MY GOD.

619
00:29:07,958 --> 00:29:11,311
- WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN? TO HELL
AND BACK? - YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.

620
00:29:11,345 --> 00:29:13,313
I'VE BEEN BAKING ON A
JOB SITE FOR THREE DAYS.

621
00:29:13,347 --> 00:29:15,398
WHY DIDN'T YOU
CALL ME, KEMOSABE?

622
00:29:15,433 --> 00:29:17,267
IT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
JUST A SHORT TRIP.

623
00:29:17,301 --> 00:29:19,268
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T GET A FREE MINUTE.

624
00:29:19,302 --> 00:29:21,320
IT'S BAD OUT THERE,
PATTY.

625
00:29:21,354 --> 00:29:23,355
KERN COUNTY QUARRY
HAD TO CLOSE DOWN

626
00:29:23,406 --> 00:29:25,357
BECAUSE THE TEAMSTERS
HAVE JOINED THE STRIKE

627
00:29:25,408 --> 00:29:27,359
AND I GOT $200,000
WORTH OF EQUIPMENT

628
00:29:27,410 --> 00:29:28,994
SITTING ON A DOCK
IN GALVESTON.

629
00:29:29,029 --> 00:29:31,146
WE CAN'T HIDE IT, MOM.
THEY'VE GOT TO START HAMMERING.

630
00:29:31,164 --> 00:29:33,414
MAN, ARE YOU BURNED.

631
00:29:33,449 --> 00:29:36,334
HIDE WHAT?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

632
00:29:36,368 --> 00:29:39,820
WELCOME TO
WOODSTOCK WEST, MAN.

633
00:29:39,838 --> 00:29:41,756
A NEW ROCK GROUP IS GONNA
BREAK HERE ON SATURDAY.

634
00:29:41,790 --> 00:29:43,708
YEAH, IT'LL HELP US GET
SOME GIGS THIS SUMMER.

635
00:29:43,759 --> 00:29:45,260
YOU HAVE A GIG
THIS SUMMER, GRANT--

636
00:29:45,294 --> 00:29:47,294
HAULING CEMENT IN ORANGE
COUNTY FOR DAVID WITZELL.

637
00:29:47,328 --> 00:29:48,795
I DON'T THINK SO.

638
00:29:48,829 --> 00:29:50,497
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE
POURING CEMENT, GRANT.

639
00:29:50,515 --> 00:29:52,933
I'M PUTTING YOU TO WORK TOO.
LOOKS LIKE YOUR SUMMER BUSINESS TRIP

640
00:29:52,967 --> 00:29:55,669
IS TO AUSTRALIA WITH BIG TODD TO
HELP HIM PICK UP SOME NEW CLIENTS.

641
00:29:55,687 --> 00:29:57,671
WAIT, HE GOES TO AUSTRALIA
AND I SHOVEL CEMENT?

642
00:29:57,689 --> 00:29:59,172
DO I LOOK LIKE
CEMENT GUY?

643
00:29:59,190 --> 00:30:01,141
DO I LOOK LIKE
ARISTOTLE ONASSIS?

644
00:30:01,175 --> 00:30:02,942
- WHO DO YOU THINK PAYS
FOR ALL THIS? - WE DID.

645
00:30:02,976 --> 00:30:04,510
- YOU DID?
- YES.

646
00:30:04,528 --> 00:30:05,978
REALLY?
WITH WHAT MONEY?

647
00:30:06,012 --> 00:30:07,647
THE MONEY MOM GAVE US
FOR DOING CHORES.

648
00:30:07,681 --> 00:30:09,065
WHERE DO YOU THINK
MOM GETS HER MONEY?

649
00:30:09,116 --> 00:30:11,400
WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES THAT MAKE?

650
00:30:12,686 --> 00:30:14,820
WHY DON'T WE
DISCUSS THIS LATER?

651
00:30:25,464 --> 00:30:28,250
WHY WEREN'T YOU
WEARING A SHIRT?

652
00:30:30,086 --> 00:30:33,087
IT WAS A 110°.

653
00:30:33,138 --> 00:30:35,422
I DIDN'T KNOW
THE SUN WAS SO HOT.

654
00:30:39,043 --> 00:30:41,562
THAT FEELS NICE

655
00:30:41,596 --> 00:30:44,064
WHEN YOU TOUCH ME
LIKE THAT.

656
00:30:51,238 --> 00:30:53,189
WHY'D YOU STOP?

657
00:30:54,441 --> 00:30:57,160
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT
TO GIVE YOU THE WRONG IDEA.

658
00:30:57,194 --> 00:30:59,195
WHAT IDEA IS THAT?

659
00:30:59,229 --> 00:31:01,363
THAT EVERYTHING
IS OKAY WITH US.

660
00:31:02,949 --> 00:31:06,952
YOU PROMISED ME THAT IF WE DID
THIS SHOW YOU'D BE HOME MORE.

661
00:31:10,340 --> 00:31:13,208
YOU KNOW, I WAS FLYING
BACK HERE THINKING

