736
00:36:05,064 --> 00:36:07,983
¶ WE DON'T GET FOOLED
AGAIN... ¶

737
00:36:33,807 --> 00:36:36,809
PAT LOUD?
THE PAT LOUD?

738
00:36:36,844 --> 00:36:39,811
I'M CRAIG GILBERT FROM NEW YORK.
I'M A BIG FAN.

739
00:36:39,846 --> 00:36:42,347
I THOUGHT
FANS WERE LOYAL.

740
00:36:42,381 --> 00:36:44,382
IT'S REALLY BEEN
QUITE A WHILE, YOU KNOW?

741
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:46,518
I KNOW, I KNOW.
I COULDN'T GET AWAY.

742
00:36:46,552 --> 00:36:48,520
BUT I'VE BEEN WATCHING YOU
EVERY DAY IN DAILIES

743
00:36:48,554 --> 00:36:50,389
AND YOU ARE AMAZING
IN EVERY FRAME.

744
00:36:50,423 --> 00:36:53,407
ARE ALL MEN BULLSHITTERS, CRAIG,
OR JUST THE ONES IN MY LIFE?

745
00:36:59,615 --> 00:37:01,866
FOR A GROUP TO ATTAIN
SUPER STARDOM,

746
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:03,668
THEY HAVE TO BE
ABOUT ONE PERSON.

747
00:37:03,702 --> 00:37:06,403
NOW, THE SUPREMES HAVE IT.
THE EMOTIONS DON'T.

748
00:37:06,421 --> 00:37:08,738
SO DO THESE KIDS STAND
A CHANCE AT MAKING IT?

749
00:37:08,756 --> 00:37:11,124
- I'M TOM, BY THE WAY--
PATTY'S BROTHER. - HELLO.

750
00:37:11,175 --> 00:37:13,543
SURE, THEY'RE GREAT. THEY
SHOULD DEFINITELY STICK WITH IT.

751
00:37:13,577 --> 00:37:16,596
OH, NOW THAT'S EASY FOR
A GUY WITH NO KIDS TO SAY.

752
00:37:16,631 --> 00:37:19,599
LIFE'S ALL ABOUT CHASING
YOUR DREAMS, RIGHT?

753
00:37:19,634 --> 00:37:23,135
WHY, I EVEN GOT ONE WHO THINKS
I'M GONNA FLY HIM OFF TO PARIS.

754
00:37:23,186 --> 00:37:25,437
WELL, ACTUALLY
HE'S IN PARIS.

755
00:37:25,472 --> 00:37:26,689
HE'S WHAT?

756
00:37:26,723 --> 00:37:28,774
AND I SENT A CINEMATOGRAPHER
OFF AFTER HIM.

757
00:37:28,808 --> 00:37:30,592
GOOD FOR OLD LANCE.

758
00:37:30,610 --> 00:37:33,929
HE GOT SOMEONE TO PAY FOR
A TRIP OTHER THAN HIS OLD MAN.

759
00:37:33,947 --> 00:37:36,231
FINE BY ME.

760
00:37:36,265 --> 00:37:38,316
- ALAN.
- WELL, IT'S NOT FINE BY ME.

761
00:37:38,367 --> 00:37:40,485
AND I'D LIKE TO SEE
THAT PARIS FOOTAGE.

762
00:37:40,536 --> 00:37:43,270
IN FACT, I'D LIKE TO SEE
ALL THE FOOTAGE AND FIND OUT

763
00:37:43,288 --> 00:37:45,490
WHAT THE HELL ELSE
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT MY FAMILY

764
00:37:45,541 --> 00:37:48,609
AND WHAT YOU'RE AIMING FOR
WITH ANY OF THIS.

765
00:37:48,627 --> 00:37:50,328
ALL RIGHT.

766
00:37:50,379 --> 00:37:52,329
THINK OF A SPACESHIP
LANDING ON EARTH

767
00:37:52,380 --> 00:37:54,865
1,000 YEARS FROM NOW
AND FINDING A TIME CAPSULE.

768
00:37:54,899 --> 00:37:57,134
AND INSIDE THAT TIME
CAPSULE IS A FILM.

769
00:37:57,168 --> 00:37:59,169
AND ON THE FILM
EVERYONE IS SMILING

770
00:37:59,220 --> 00:38:01,922
AND SAFE IN THE CERTAINTY
OF EACH OTHER'S LOVE.

771
00:38:01,956 --> 00:38:03,890
BUT AS IT TURNS OUT,
ALL THE ALIENS FOUND

772
00:38:03,925 --> 00:38:08,227
WAS AN OLD EPISODE OF
"THE PARTRIDGE FAMILY."

773
00:38:08,261 --> 00:38:11,313
NOW IS THAT WHAT WE REALLY
WANT TO LEAVE BEHIND AS A CULTURE--

774
00:38:11,348 --> 00:38:15,300
SOMETHING THAT'S THE COMPLETE
ANTITHESIS OF HOW WE REALLY LIVE,

775
00:38:15,318 --> 00:38:18,521
FUMBLING AROUND
IN CONFUSION?

776
00:38:18,572 --> 00:38:20,739
OH, THAT'S
FULL OF SHIT.

777
00:38:20,773 --> 00:38:23,408
FUMBLING AROUND
IN CONFUSION?

778
00:38:23,442 --> 00:38:25,476
THE LOUDS
ARE NOT CONFUSED

779
00:38:25,494 --> 00:38:27,162
AND WE ARE NOT
FUMBLING AROUND.

780
00:38:27,196 --> 00:38:28,646
I AM FINE.

781
00:38:28,664 --> 00:38:31,149
MY FAMILY IS FINE.

782
00:38:31,167 --> 00:38:32,951
I AM GOING TO COME
TO THE MOTEL

783
00:38:32,985 --> 00:38:34,836
TO LOOK AT SOME FOOTAGE
TOMORROW, CRAIG.

784
00:38:34,870 --> 00:38:37,588
AND IF THERE'S ANYTHING ABOUT
IT THAT GIVES A FALSE IMPRESSION

785
00:38:37,622 --> 00:38:40,708
THAT WE ARE STRUGGLING
TO MAKE SENSE OF OUR LIVES,

786
00:38:40,759 --> 00:38:43,010
IT'S NOT GOING
ON THE AIR.

787
00:38:56,473 --> 00:38:58,057
Who did that?

788
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:03,913
Our sons
are criminals.

789
00:39:03,947 --> 00:39:06,398
I have to wash my hair
again tonight.

790
00:39:09,452 --> 00:39:11,903
THERE'S 86,000'
OF FILM THERE, PAT,

791
00:39:11,954 --> 00:39:13,488
EVERY FRAME
AS GOOD AS THAT.

792
00:39:13,522 --> 00:39:15,657
NOW WE COULD
SIT HERE FOR DAYS

793
00:39:15,691 --> 00:39:18,026
AND I'D BE HAPPY TO DO THAT
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT TO DO--

794
00:39:18,044 --> 00:39:20,527
NO, THAT WON'T BE
NECESSARY.

795
00:39:20,545 --> 00:39:23,363
I'LL SEND A PROJECTOR OVER
WHEN THE PARIS FOOTAGE COMES IN.

796
00:39:27,202 --> 00:39:30,171
I WANT TO APOLOGIZE
FOR LAST NIGHT.

797
00:39:30,205 --> 00:39:32,423
I'VE BEEN HAVING
KIND OF A TOUGH TIME.

798
00:39:32,474 --> 00:39:34,707
WELL, THAT'S CLEAR TO SEE.

799
00:39:39,713 --> 00:39:42,816
ARE YOU AND BILL
HAVING PROBLEMS?

800
00:39:42,850 --> 00:39:45,485
THE PAINFUL TRUTH IS

801
00:39:45,519 --> 00:39:49,772
THAT YES, WE HAVE HAD
A ROCKY PAST AND...

802
00:39:49,823 --> 00:39:53,058
NOW I'M NOT SURE
WHERE WE ARE.

803
00:39:55,328 --> 00:39:57,896
WELL, I CAN'T
SPEAK FOR BILL,

804
00:39:57,914 --> 00:39:59,915
BUT THE PAT LOUD
THAT I SEE IS A VISION

805
00:39:59,949 --> 00:40:02,334
OF A LIBERATED MODERN WOMAN.

806
00:40:02,368 --> 00:40:04,836
PANTSUITS WILL DO THAT.

807
00:40:08,340 --> 00:40:12,293
IN FACT,
I SEE A ROLE MODEL.

808
00:40:12,344 --> 00:40:14,512
WOMEN ALL ACROSS AMERICA
ARE GOING TO LOOK TO YOU

809
00:40:14,546 --> 00:40:18,915
FOR A ROADMAP OF HOW TO BE
AND WHO TO BE.

810
00:40:18,933 --> 00:40:21,351
YOU'RE IN THE POSITION
TO SHOW WOMEN,

811
00:40:21,385 --> 00:40:23,419
WHOSE STRENGTH
IS ERODING,

812
00:40:23,437 --> 00:40:26,022
HOW TO TAKE BACK
THEIR LIVES.

813
00:40:28,926 --> 00:40:32,279
AS USUAL,
YOU ARE VERY ELOQUENT.

814
00:40:32,313 --> 00:40:34,647
WELL, LAST NIGHT YOU ASKED ME
IF I WAS A BULLSHITTER.

815
00:40:34,698 --> 00:40:36,816
ARE YOU?

816
00:40:38,151 --> 00:40:40,286
TEST ME.

817
00:40:41,938 --> 00:40:45,708
WHEN WE FIRST MET I TOLD YOU
WHAT I THOUGHT OF YOU.

818
00:40:45,742 --> 00:40:48,276
WHAT DID YOU THINK
OF ME?

819
00:40:49,995 --> 00:40:53,381
I THOUGHT,

820
00:40:53,415 --> 00:40:57,752
"IF THAT GUY CAN FIX
HIS FLABBY BODY,

821
00:40:57,786 --> 00:41:00,338
I'VE MET
MY PERFECT MAN."

822
00:41:06,227 --> 00:41:08,929
I ALWAYS FANTASIZED THAT IF
I COULD FIND THE RIGHT MAN,

823
00:41:08,963 --> 00:41:10,731
I'D LEAVE HIM.

824
00:41:10,765 --> 00:41:12,816
BECAUSE I CANNOT
LIVE ALONE.

825
00:41:12,851 --> 00:41:16,736
I ABSOLUTELY
CAN'T DO IT.

826
00:41:16,770 --> 00:41:18,738
I'M GOING THROUGH THIS
STAGE IN MY LIFE NOW

827
00:41:18,772 --> 00:41:20,523
WHERE LANCE HAS LEFT.

828
00:41:20,574 --> 00:41:23,075
SOON THE REST OF MY KIDS
WILL FOLLOW.

829
00:41:23,110 --> 00:41:25,194
AND WHAT
HAVE I GOT LEFT?

830
00:41:25,245 --> 00:41:28,231
I HAVEN'T GOT
ANYTHING LEFT.

831
00:41:28,265 --> 00:41:30,900
IT SCARES ME
TO DEATH.

832
00:41:39,792 --> 00:41:43,494
- HEY. - DON'T TALK.
JUST LISTEN.

833
00:41:43,512 --> 00:41:45,496
I PROMISED THE GIRLS
A TRIP TO TAOS.

834
00:41:45,514 --> 00:41:47,882
WE'LL GO AS SOON
AS SCHOOL'S OUT.

835
00:41:47,933 --> 00:41:49,767
I WANT DELILAH TO HAVE
A BREAK FROM BRAD.

836
00:41:49,801 --> 00:41:51,886
SHE CAN TAKE
A FRIEND INSTEAD.

837
00:41:51,937 --> 00:41:54,104
I'LL FIND A HORSE
FOR MICHELE TO RIDE.

838
00:41:54,139 --> 00:41:56,774
GRANT'S WILLING TO GIVE IT
A TRY IN ORANGE COUNTY

839
00:41:56,808 --> 00:41:59,193
SHOVELING CEMENT.

840
00:41:59,227 --> 00:42:02,562
AND KEVIN WILL ACCOMPANY
TODD MAN TO AUSTRALIA.

841
00:42:02,613 --> 00:42:04,981
WELL, IT'S ABOUT TIME
SOMEBODY LISTENED TO ME.

