00:42:05,015 --> 00:42:06,816
NOBODY'S LISTENING TO YOU.

843
00:42:06,850 --> 00:42:09,953
I JUST WANT EVERYONE
ACCOUNTED FOR BEFORE I GO,

844
00:42:09,987 --> 00:42:12,188
SO NO ONE'S IN DANGER
OF DESERTION.

845
00:42:12,206 --> 00:42:16,074
SO NOW GOING TO WORK
IS DESERTION TO YOU?

846
00:42:18,077 --> 00:42:20,996
I'M GOING AWAY
TO GET SOME CLARITY

847
00:42:21,030 --> 00:42:23,698
ABOUT WHAT IS REAL
AND WHAT ISN'T.

848
00:42:23,716 --> 00:42:27,869
I THINK IT'S A GOOD IDEA
TO GET AWAY, PAT.

849
00:42:29,038 --> 00:42:31,172
I'M SURE YOU DO.

850
00:42:34,059 --> 00:42:36,210
YOU THINK THAT'S GOING
TO RIDE ALL RIGHT, HUH?

851
00:42:41,266 --> 00:42:45,318
- BYE-BYE, LITTLE DARLING.
- BYE, DAD.  I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

852
00:42:45,353 --> 00:42:47,437
I LEFT THE NUMBER OF
THE HOUSE WE'RE STAYING AT.

853
00:42:47,488 --> 00:42:50,390
I EXPECT YOU TO CALL ME COLLECT
AS SOON AS YOU GET TO AUSTRALIA.

854
00:42:50,408 --> 00:42:52,558
- ALL RIGHT?
- I WILL.

855
00:42:53,894 --> 00:42:57,998
- BYE. - WHEN DO YOU
COME TO TAOS?

856
00:42:58,032 --> 00:43:00,332
OH, FOR GOD'S SAKE,
YOU CAN ANSWER ME.

857
00:43:00,367 --> 00:43:03,568
- WE'LL FLY UP OVER THE WEEKEND.
- NEAT.

858
00:43:03,586 --> 00:43:05,287
WHO AM I GONNA TAKE
TO THE FIESTA DAY PARADE?

859
00:43:05,338 --> 00:43:07,172
OH WELL, I MIGHT BE
BACK BY THEN, SO...

860
00:43:07,207 --> 00:43:08,791
THE HECK YOU WILL.

861
00:43:08,842 --> 00:43:11,293
MOM, YOU SAID THAT IF I REALLY
MISSED BRAD THAT I COULD COME BACK.

862
00:43:11,344 --> 00:43:13,595
I MADE LUNCH FOR
ALL YOU GUYS BY THE POOL.

863
00:43:13,630 --> 00:43:15,596
- BYE, GRANT.
- BYE.

864
00:43:15,631 --> 00:43:17,915
- BYE, KEVIN.
- DELILAH.

865
00:43:17,933 --> 00:43:20,051
- BYE, DELILAH.
- BYE, BRAD.

866
00:43:20,085 --> 00:43:21,719
BYE, BRAD.

867
00:43:21,753 --> 00:43:24,088
OH, I LOVE YOU, BRAD.

868
00:43:29,944 --> 00:43:32,279
NO, RAY DAVIES.
I'M TELLING YOU.

869
00:43:32,313 --> 00:43:34,982
- RAY DAVIES.
- RAY DAVIES?

870
00:43:35,033 --> 00:43:36,733
I DON'T LIKE HIM AS MUCH.

871
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:40,570
- "CHANGES" IS GOOD.
- "LIFE ON MARS."

872
00:43:40,604 --> 00:43:43,322
"LIFE ON MARS" IS GOOD.

873
00:43:43,373 --> 00:43:45,574
ALAN, SUSAN,

874
00:43:45,608 --> 00:43:48,327
I'M HEADING DOWN TO MY
OFFICE IN ABOUT AN HOUR

875
00:43:48,378 --> 00:43:50,129
AND IF YOU WANT
TO COME ALONG,

876
00:43:50,163 --> 00:43:53,949
I'VE GOT SOME PRETTY INTERESTING
STUFF COMING DOWN THE PIKE TODAY.

877
00:43:53,967 --> 00:43:56,618
THEY'RE FILMING ME BUYING
A NEW BUSINESS SUIT, DAD.

878
00:43:56,636 --> 00:43:58,303
YEAH, AND THEN
BAND PRACTICE.

879
00:43:58,337 --> 00:44:01,556
WELL, THAT'S A GOOD DEAL.

880
00:44:01,590 --> 00:44:03,508
MAYBE TOMORROW, BILL.

881
00:44:12,351 --> 00:44:13,751
HELLO.

882
00:44:13,785 --> 00:44:17,137
- CRAIG, IT'S BILL.
- Bill... hi.

883
00:44:17,155 --> 00:44:19,073
DID THEY
GET OFF OKAY?

884
00:44:19,107 --> 00:44:20,807
They did, a few hours ago.

885
00:44:20,825 --> 00:44:24,028
LISTEN, HOW LONG
ARE YOU AROUND FOR?

886
00:44:24,079 --> 00:44:25,662
I'M OUT ON A RED-EYE.
WHY?

887
00:44:25,697 --> 00:44:27,864
I WAS WONDERING IF YOU
COULD DO ME A FAVOR TODAY.

888
00:44:27,915 --> 00:44:30,816
WELL, IF IT'S
IN MY POWER, SURE.

889
00:44:30,834 --> 00:44:33,786
WELL, CRAIG,
I HAVE A FRIEND

890
00:44:33,820 --> 00:44:36,039
who would like to get
into show business.

891
00:44:36,090 --> 00:44:38,091
YOU DON'T ACTUALLY
HAVE TO DO ANYTHING.

892
00:44:38,125 --> 00:44:40,009
JUST GIVE HER SOME ADVICE.

893
00:44:40,044 --> 00:44:42,544
ON THE OTHER HAND, IF YOU CAN
DO SOMETHING, THAT'D BE GREAT.

894
00:44:42,595 --> 00:44:44,162
PERSONALLY I THINK
SHE'S A KNOCKOUT.

895
00:44:44,180 --> 00:44:46,965
IT'S CLEAR TO YOU I'M NOT
THAT KIND OF PRODUCER, RIGHT?

896
00:44:46,999 --> 00:44:50,352
- BUT SHE DOESN'T HAVE
TO KNOW THAT. - YEAH.

897
00:44:50,386 --> 00:44:52,504
AND PATTY DOESN'T HAVE
TO KNOW ABOUT THIS EITHER.

898
00:44:52,522 --> 00:44:54,506
I HAVEN'T BEEN
AN ANGEL, CRAIG,

899
00:44:54,524 --> 00:44:56,673
BUT I'M SURE YOU'VE
FIGURED THAT OUT,

900
00:44:56,691 --> 00:45:00,895
CONSIDERING ALL THE TIME YOU
TWO HAVE BEEN SPENDING TOGETHER.

901
00:45:03,398 --> 00:45:06,984
ANYWAY, I LEARNED THE HARD
WAY TO BE VERY CAREFUL,

902
00:45:07,018 --> 00:45:09,987
KEEP ANY SOUVENIRS THAT MIGHT
GET HER STARTED OUT OF SIGHT.

903
00:45:10,021 --> 00:45:12,355
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
"SOUVENIRS"?

904
00:45:12,373 --> 00:45:14,707
WELL, YOU KNOW,
MATCHBOOKS,

905
00:45:14,742 --> 00:45:17,494
SWIZZLE STICKS,
PHOTOS--

906
00:45:17,528 --> 00:45:18,995
STUFF TO LOOK BACK ON

907
00:45:19,029 --> 00:45:21,047
AND SEE THAT THERE WAS
MORE TO THAT BILL LOUD GUY

908
00:45:21,082 --> 00:45:23,049
THAN JUST SOME PACK MULE
SLAVING AWAY

909
00:45:23,084 --> 00:45:25,535
FOR EVERYBODY ELSE'S SHOT
AT SELF-FULFILLMENT.

910
00:45:25,553 --> 00:45:29,371
WELL, LIKE I'VE SAID,
EVERY HUSBAND DESERVES A HIDING PLACE.

911
00:45:29,389 --> 00:45:32,057
THEY'VE GOT IT FIGURED
OUT RIGHT IN EUROPE--

912
00:45:32,092 --> 00:45:34,359
A MAN'S A MAN
AND FAMILY'S SACRED.

913
00:45:34,394 --> 00:45:36,512
BUT A MAN
IN YOUR SITUATION,

914
00:45:36,546 --> 00:45:38,514
YOUR MARRIAGE BEING
WHAT IT IS,

915
00:45:38,548 --> 00:45:41,682
YOU PROBABLY UNDERSTAND
THAT MORE THAN ANYBODY.

916
00:45:44,236 --> 00:45:47,355
I KNOW I'M SHAPING UP TO BE
THE SQUARE OF YOUR SHOW.

917
00:45:47,389 --> 00:45:50,441
MAYBE I'VE GOT MORE
GOING ON THAN YOU THINK.

918
00:45:59,083 --> 00:46:01,535
SALLY IS LIKE
A SISTER TO ME.

919
00:46:03,171 --> 00:46:05,405
- YEAH.
- A BAD SISTER.

920
00:46:07,708 --> 00:46:12,011
SO DOESN'T SHE PHOTOGRAPH
GREAT, CRAIG?

921
00:46:12,045 --> 00:46:15,364
- DON'T YOU THINK?
- OH, BILLY, THAT ONE?

922
00:46:15,398 --> 00:46:17,349
- VERY LOVELY.
- THANKS.

923
00:46:17,384 --> 00:46:19,135
YOU KNOW WHAT I TELL HER
THE PROBLEM IS?

924
00:46:19,186 --> 00:46:21,253
TOO MUCH LIKE
BRIGITTE BARDOT.

925
00:46:21,271 --> 00:46:24,256
YES.
YES, I SEE THAT.

926
00:46:24,274 --> 00:46:27,058
DO YOUR THING,
YOU KNOW, THE--

927
00:46:27,092 --> 00:46:28,943
- OH BILLY.
- GO AHEAD.

928
00:46:28,978 --> 00:46:31,095
OKAY.

929
00:46:33,649 --> 00:46:36,484
"AND I, OF LADIES

930
00:46:36,535 --> 00:46:38,820
MOST DEJECT
AND WRETCHED,

931
00:46:38,871 --> 00:46:42,439
THAT SUCKED THE HONEY
OF HIS MUSIC VOWS,

932
00:46:42,457 --> 00:46:45,659
NOW SEE THAT NOBLE
AND MOST SOVEREIGN REASON

933
00:46:45,710 --> 00:46:48,795
LIKE SWEET BELLS JANGLED

934
00:46:48,830 --> 00:46:51,632
OUT OF TUNE AND HARSH,
THAT--"

935
00:46:51,666 --> 00:46:54,250
YEAH.

936
00:46:54,284 --> 00:46:56,552
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT MEANS,
BUT I THINK IT'S GREAT.

937
00:46:56,587 --> 00:46:58,821
IT'S OPHELIA.

938
00:46:58,856 --> 00:47:00,139
- VERY NICE.
- THANK YOU.

939
00:47:00,174 --> 00:47:02,642
- SHAKESPEARE.
- AH.

940
00:47:02,676 --> 00:47:04,644
SO WHAT DO YOU
THINK, CRAIG?

941
00:47:04,678 --> 00:47:08,264
I THINK I MIGHT KNOW SOMEONE THAT
WOULD BE QUITE INTERESTED IN THESE.

942
00:47:18,157 --> 00:47:22,994
¶ SHE'S BOUGHT A HAT
LIKE PRINCESS MARINA'S ¶

943
00:47:23,029 --> 00:47:27,481
¶ AND HER NEIGHBORS THINK
IT SUITS HER A TREAT ¶

944
00:47:27,499 --> 00:47:30,651
¶ BUT SHE HASN'T
ANY FOOD ¶

945
00:47:30,669 --> 00:47:32,820
¶ IN THE WHOLE LARDER ¶

946
00:47:32,854 --> 00:47:35,506
¶ NOR HAS ANYBODY ELSE ¶

947
00:47:35,540 --> 00:47:38,008
¶ IN THE STREET ¶

948
00:47:38,042 --> 00:47:40,493
¶ BUT SHE SMILES
AND YOU'D THINK ¶

949
00:47:40,511 --> 00:47:42,962
¶ SHE WAS WEALTHY ¶

950
00:47:42,996 --> 00:47:47,166
¶ SHE SMILES JUST LIKE
A REAL MILLIONAIRE... ¶

951
00:47:47,184 --> 00:47:50,336
- OBVIOUSLY HE DOESN'T KNOW THERE'S
A CAMERA THERE. - MY BROTHER'S SO SHY.

952
00:47:50,354 --> 00:47:53,555
¶ ...PRINCESS MARINA ¶

953
00:47:53,606 --> 00:47:57,809
- ¶ 'CAUSE SHE DON'T CARE. ¶
- Pat: OH YEAH.

954
00:47:57,843 --> 00:48:00,312
LET'S HEAR IT
FOR LANCE LOUD.

955
00:48:00,346 --> 00:48:03,615
- GO LANCE!
- I LIKED IT.

956
00:48:03,650 --> 00:48:05,817
MOM.

957
00:48:05,851 --> 00:48:07,851
PLEASE TELL ME YOU'RE NOT
ABOUT TO START WHINING.

958
00:48:07,869 --> 00:48:09,820
WELL, YOU SAID THAT
WE COULD TALK ABOUT IT.

959
00:48:09,854 --> 00:48:11,906
AFTER JUST 10 DAYS,
DELILAH?

960
00:48:11,957 --> 00:48:13,741
MOM, 10 DAYS IN TAOS
IS AN ETERNITY.

961
00:48:13,792 --> 00:48:16,994
MISS LOUD, MY MOM SAID I CAN TAKE
THE BUS BACK IF DELILAH COMES WITH.

962
00:48:17,028 --> 00:48:19,196
- HELLO?
- WHO IS IT, SWEETIE?

963
00:48:19,214 --> 00:48:21,499
HI.
MR. GILBERT.

964
00:48:21,533 --> 00:48:24,718
DAD SAID THAT WE COULD COME BACK
WHENEVER WE WANTED, JUST CALL ANYTIME.

965
00:48:24,752 --> 00:48:26,836
HE SAID HE'D HAVE DINNER
ON THE TABLE.  MOM.

966
00:48:26,870 --> 00:48:28,805
FINE.
TAKE THE BUS TOMORROW.

967
00:48:28,839 --> 00:48:30,090
YES!

968
00:48:30,141 --> 00:48:32,809
AT LAST,
A GROWNUP TO TALK TO.

969
00:48:32,843 --> 00:48:35,312
- HOW'S YOUR TRIP?
- Fine.

970
00:48:35,346 --> 00:48:38,013
I was kind of hoping that you
might turn up here tomorrow.

971
00:48:38,047 --> 00:48:41,717
- Why? - FEELING A LITTLE SULTRY,
I GUESS.

972
00:48:41,735 --> 00:48:43,819
Listen, this is...

973
00:48:43,853 --> 00:48:47,222
VERY HARD FOR ME
TO DISCUSS.

974
00:48:47,240 --> 00:48:51,442
I'VE BEEN DEBATING
WHETHER TO CALL OR NOT.

975
00:48:51,493 --> 00:48:54,061
But as a friend,
I felt that I should.

976
00:48:54,079 --> 00:48:56,731
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT'S WRONG?

977
00:48:56,749 --> 00:48:59,284
I saw Bill
before I left

978
00:48:59,335 --> 00:49:02,637
AND HE TOOK ME
FOR A RIDE TO MALIBU

979
00:49:02,671 --> 00:49:04,372
to see a friend.

980
00:49:04,406 --> 00:49:06,623
WHO?
ANDY PLATT?

981
00:49:06,674 --> 00:49:08,625
NO NO, NOT ANDY PLATT.

982
00:49:08,676 --> 00:49:11,378
HER NAME WAS SALLY.

983
00:49:11,412 --> 00:49:14,298
And she gave me
an 8x10 glossy

984
00:49:14,349 --> 00:49:17,301
AND A TAPE OF HER SINGING
"THE SOUND OF MUSIC."

985
00:49:21,004 --> 00:49:23,939
LOOK, I CAN FLY OUT
TO SANTA BARBARA TOMORROW

986
00:49:23,974 --> 00:49:25,891
AND YOU CAN
MEET ME THERE

987
00:49:25,925 --> 00:49:27,593
and we'll talk
things through.

988
00:49:27,611 --> 00:49:29,478
I understand
what you're feeling.

989
00:49:29,529 --> 00:49:34,650
I'M STILL RAW
FROM MY OWN SITUATION.

990
00:49:36,452 --> 00:49:39,154
- Patty.
- WE'RE FILMING TOMORROW.

991
00:49:39,205 --> 00:49:41,323
WELL, I'M THE PRODUCER.
I CAN CHANGE THE SCHEDULE.

992
00:49:41,374 --> 00:49:42,824
No.

993
00:49:42,875 --> 00:49:45,160
IF SINGING SALLY
EVER SEES ME ON TV,

994
00:49:45,211 --> 00:49:48,296
I WANT HER TO SEE ME HERE
IN THIS BEAUTIFUL PLACE.

995
00:49:58,823 --> 00:50:01,058
HONESTLY, IF I HEAR
ANOTHER ACCORDION,

996
00:50:01,076 --> 00:50:03,344
I'M GOING TO VOMIT ALL
OVER THIS TABLE. I REALLY AM.

997
00:50:03,378 --> 00:50:06,279
I'M SERIOUS, CAN'T YOU ASK
YOUR FATHER FOR MORE MONEY?

998
00:50:06,330 --> 00:50:08,064
I'M GETTING BORED HERE.

999
00:50:08,082 --> 00:50:10,066
BORED IN PARIS-- WHO KNEW
THAT WAS POSSIBLE?

1000
00:50:10,084 --> 00:50:12,418
I ACTUALLY MISS
SANTA BARBARA.

1001
00:50:14,571 --> 00:50:18,140
In Santa Barbara, firefighters
continue to battle a wildfire

1002
00:50:18,158 --> 00:50:20,409
that started in the ridges
above Mountain Drive.

1003
00:50:20,443 --> 00:50:22,644
One home has been lost
and many more are threatened.

1004
00:50:22,662 --> 00:50:25,497
Police and firemen
are evacuating residents...

1005
00:50:29,202 --> 00:50:32,087
OH, MOM, IT'S BURNING
AROUND HERE.

1006
00:50:32,121 --> 00:50:33,955
I'm here alone.
I don't know what to do.

1007
00:50:33,989 --> 00:50:35,456
PUT YOUR FATHER
ON THE PHONE.

1008
00:50:35,490 --> 00:50:37,375
NO, HE'S NOT HERE EITHER.
HE DIDN'T SHOW UP.

1009
00:50:37,426 --> 00:50:39,093
- WHAT?
- He called to say

1010
00:50:39,127 --> 00:50:41,095
THAT HE WAS AWAY ON BUSINESS,
BUT HE WOULDN'T SAY WHERE.

1011
00:50:41,129 --> 00:50:43,848
SON OF A BITCH. LISTEN,
GET THE HELL OUT OF THERE.

1012
00:50:43,882 --> 00:50:46,100
- THE POLICE ARE HERE.
- I'm still 10 hours away.

1013
00:50:46,134 --> 00:50:48,219
OH, MOM, I THINK
THE COPS ARE HERE FOR US.

1014
00:50:48,270 --> 00:50:50,720
GO GO.
FOR GOD'S SAKE, GO.

1015
00:51:07,036 --> 00:51:08,720
MOM!

1016
00:51:11,040 --> 00:51:12,908
GRANT.

1017
00:51:12,959 --> 00:51:14,910
- OH BABIES.
- MOM.

1018
00:51:14,961 --> 00:51:16,712
- DELILAH. - MOM, THE ENTIRE
HILL WAS BURNING.

1019
00:51:16,746 --> 00:51:19,080
I WAS SO WORRIED.

1020
00:51:19,131 --> 00:51:20,832
- WE'RE OKAY.
- IT'S OKAY, MOM.

1021
00:51:20,866 --> 00:51:22,383
I'M FINE.
REALLY, IT'S OKAY.

1022
00:51:22,418 --> 00:51:25,720
- OH MY GOD.
- MOM, LANCE IS COMING HOME.

1023
00:51:25,754 --> 00:51:27,204
WHAT?

1024
00:51:27,222 --> 00:51:29,674
MY BABIES
ARE COMING HOME.

1025
00:51:38,316 --> 00:51:40,717
A TRUE UNIDENTIFIED
FLYING OBJECT.

1026
00:51:40,735 --> 00:51:43,219
OH MY GOSH.

1027
00:51:43,237 --> 00:51:46,106
WHO IS THIS?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

1028
00:51:48,158 --> 00:51:51,243
HI!  YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

1029
00:51:51,278 --> 00:51:53,162
- I FOUND THIS IN FRANCE.
- OH MY GOD.

1030
00:51:53,196 --> 00:51:55,080
I THOUGHT YOU'D LIKE IT.
YOU CAN THROW IT ON.

1031
00:51:55,115 --> 00:51:57,166
YOU CAN WEAR IT
FOR A CONCERT,

1032
00:51:57,200 --> 00:52:00,035
JUST TO REALLY SPARK UP
SANTA BARBARA AND ALL THAT.

1033
00:52:00,069 --> 00:52:02,071
HEY, DAD'S HOME.

1034
00:52:04,807 --> 00:52:06,541
WELL, IT'S
THE LONE RANGER.

1035
00:52:06,575 --> 00:52:08,927
- HI, DAD.
- MY WORLD TRAVELER.

1036
00:52:08,961 --> 00:52:10,845
HI.

1037
00:52:10,880 --> 00:52:12,430
HOW ARE YOU DOING?
YOU LOOK GOOD.

1038
00:52:12,465 --> 00:52:14,382
OH WAIT, LOOK.
I GOT YOU A PRESENT.

1039
00:52:14,416 --> 00:52:17,434
OH, THANK YOU, LANCE.

1040
00:52:17,469 --> 00:52:19,436
THAT'S A SHARP-LOOKING
TIE THERE, LANCE.

1041
00:52:19,471 --> 00:52:21,555
- YOU LIKE IT?
- IT SURE IS.  YEAH.

1042
00:52:21,589 --> 00:52:23,757
- IT HAS LOTS OF COLORS.
- THANK YOU.

1043
00:52:23,775 --> 00:52:25,726
THAT'S FOR YOU.

1044
00:52:25,760 --> 00:52:27,478
OOH, WHAT'S THIS,
KEMOSABE?

1045
00:52:27,529 --> 00:52:29,947
$300,000 WORTH
OF SHOVEL TEETH.

1046
00:52:29,981 --> 00:52:32,315
THAT'S MORE THAN WORTH
THE WEEKEND

1047
00:52:32,366 --> 00:52:34,984
IN THE HELL HOLE OF FRESNO,
WOULDN'T YOU SAY?

1048
00:52:35,035 --> 00:52:37,954
WELL, I'M SURE
IT WAS HELL, BILL.

1049
00:52:37,988 --> 00:52:40,373
SAY, ISN'T THIS
FIESTA DAY?

1050
00:52:40,407 --> 00:52:41,908
WHO WANTS TO GO
TO THE PARADE?

1051
00:52:41,942 --> 00:52:43,059
PATTY?

1052
00:52:43,093 --> 00:52:45,628
WELL, I'M SHOPPING
FOR HELEN HARRISON.

1053
00:52:45,662 --> 00:52:47,612
YOU KNOW, HER HOUSE
BURNED DOWN.

1054
00:52:47,630 --> 00:52:49,831
OH YEAH, I HEARD
ABOUT THE FIRE.

1055
00:52:49,882 --> 00:52:51,449
YEAH, I ALMOST DIED.

1056
00:52:51,467 --> 00:52:53,835
YOU ALMOST DIED?
WOW.

1057
00:52:53,886 --> 00:52:55,887
WELL, THAT'S AWFUL,
BIG D.

1058
00:52:55,922 --> 00:52:58,490
WHEN I GOT HERE ON WEDNESDAY,
THE WHOLE PATIO WAS COVERED IN ASH.

1059
00:52:58,524 --> 00:53:00,559
IS THAT WHY
THAT POOL'S SO GREEN?

1060
00:53:00,593 --> 00:53:02,510
NO, THAT'S ALGAE.

1061
00:53:02,561 --> 00:53:05,479
THE POOL MAN LEFT A NOTE.
HE COULDN'T GET IN.

1062
00:53:05,514 --> 00:53:07,648
APPARENTLY YOU LOCKED
THE PATIO

1063
00:53:07,682 --> 00:53:11,134
WHEN YOU WENT TO,
UM, FRESNO.

1064
00:53:11,152 --> 00:53:13,821
BY THE LOOKS OF THINGS,
THAT WAS QUITE SOME TIME AGO.

1065
00:53:13,855 --> 00:53:16,322
WELL, I MADE IT BACK
FOR FIESTA.

1066
00:53:16,357 --> 00:53:18,157
HOW ABOUT I FLIP
SOME BURGERS

1067
00:53:18,192 --> 00:53:20,142
FOR THE COMMUNITY BUFFET
AT EL PASEO TONIGHT?

1068
00:53:20,160 --> 00:53:23,530
WHY DON'T YOU DO THAT, BILL? WHY DON'T
YOU FLIP SOME BURGERS FOR THE BUFFET?

1069
00:53:23,581 --> 00:53:26,449
I'M SURE THE CREW WOULD LOVE
TO GET A NICE SHOT OF THAT.

1070
00:53:26,483 --> 00:53:28,952
YOU KNOW WHAT THE SAD
TRUTH IS?

1071
00:53:28,986 --> 00:53:30,669
THE KIDS ADORE
THEIR DADDY.

1072
00:53:30,703 --> 00:53:32,504
EVEN LANCE,
BELIEVE IT OR NOT.

1073
00:53:32,539 --> 00:53:34,039
BUT SOMEWHERE
ALONG THE LINE

1074
00:53:34,090 --> 00:53:36,041
HE LOST THE LINK
TO ANYTHING THAT'S REAL--

1075
00:53:36,092 --> 00:53:39,878
TO ME, TO THEM,
TO HIS HOME.

1076
00:53:39,929 --> 00:53:42,798
AND I'VE FINALLY GIVEN UP
ON PULLING HIM BACK.

1077
00:53:46,552 --> 00:53:48,436
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

1078
00:53:50,689 --> 00:53:53,808
WOW, THE MENU
HASN'T CHANGED.

1079
00:53:53,842 --> 00:53:57,061
OH, YOU'VE BEEN
HERE BEFORE.

1080
00:53:57,112 --> 00:54:00,146
I ACTUALLY--

1081
00:54:00,180 --> 00:54:02,399
I PICKED UP A MAN
IN THAT BAR ONCE.

1082
00:54:05,620 --> 00:54:07,203
REALLY?

1083
00:54:09,290 --> 00:54:12,358
WELL, I'M ASTONISHED.

1084
00:54:12,376 --> 00:54:13,877
WHAT, THAT I COULD
DO SUCH A THING?

1085
00:54:13,911 --> 00:54:16,378
NO, THAT YOU WOULD
TELL ME.

1086
00:54:16,413 --> 00:54:19,748
BACK WHEN I CAUGHT BILL
RUNNING AROUND,

1087
00:54:19,799 --> 00:54:23,702
HE KEPT GOING ON AND ON
ABOUT AN OPEN MARRIAGE.

1088
00:54:23,720 --> 00:54:26,305
I GUESS I WAS
ALREADY IN ONE,

1089
00:54:26,339 --> 00:54:28,724
JUST DIDN'T KNOW IT.

1090
00:54:28,758 --> 00:54:30,758
ANYWAY, HE ACTUALLY
ENCOURAGED ME

1091
00:54:30,809 --> 00:54:33,044
TO PARTICIPATE.

1092
00:54:33,062 --> 00:54:34,712
I GAVE IT A TRY.

1093
00:54:34,730 --> 00:54:37,065
IT WASN'T FOR ME.

1094
00:54:37,099 --> 00:54:38,850
AND THEN I--

1095
00:54:38,884 --> 00:54:40,818
I GAVE HIM
AN ULTIMATUM.

1096
00:54:40,853 --> 00:54:45,439
I THINK THAT MEN HANDLE
AGING DIFFERENTLY THAN WOMEN.

1097
00:54:45,490 --> 00:54:47,024
ALAN, ALAN, ALAN,
ALAN, ALAN.

1098
00:54:47,058 --> 00:54:49,059
READY?
